
Overview of adj aflare

The adj aflare has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) aflare, flaring -- (streaming or flapping or spreading wide as if in a current of air; "ran quickly, her flaring coat behind her"; "flags aflare in the breeze")
2. (1) ablaze, afire, aflame, aflare, alight, on fire -- (lighted up by or as by fire or flame; "forests set ablaze (or afire) by lightning"; "even the car's tires were aflame"; "a night aflare with fireworks"; "candles alight on the tables"; "houses on fire")
